[1] WHO: Ebola toll rises to more than 6800
Date: Mon 15 Dec 2014
Source: Yahoo News, AFP (Agence France-Presse) report [edited]
http://news.yahoo.com/ebola-toll-rises-more-6-800-191734236.html


More than 6800 people have now died from the Ebola virus, almost all of them in west Africa, the World Health Organization said Monday [15 Dec 2014].

The UN health agency reported that as of 13 Dec 2014, there had been 18 464 cases of infection from the deadly virus in Guinea, Liberia and Sierra Leone, and 6841 people had died. [346 new cases and 308 deaths in 4 days. - Mod.JW]

WHO did not provide an update of cases in other countries, but last week said the death toll remained the same: 6 in Mali, one in the United States, and 8 in Nigeria, which was declared Ebola free in October. Spain and Senegal, which have both been declared free from Ebola, meanwhile counted one case each, but no deaths....

As of the latest figures up to 7 Dec 2014, a total of 639 healthcare workers were known to have contracted the virus, and 349 of them had died, WHO said.... -- more

[Ref: WHO Ebola Situation summary -- Data published on 15 Dec 2014 [Guinea and Sierra Leone as of 13 Dec 2014 (Liberia as of 9 Dec 2014)
http://apps.who.int/gho/data/view.ebola-sitrep.ebola-summary-20141215?lang=en]

