[5] Rwanda: joins Ebola Solidarity Campaign
Date: Sun 14 Dec 2014
Source: East African Business Week [edited]
http://www.busiweek.com/index1.php?Ctp=2&pI=2416&pLv=3&srI=69&spI=221&cI=11


Rwanda operators start Ebola SMS fundraiser
-------------------------------------------
[Photo: Poster held by Dr. Binagwaho flanked by Tongai Maramba, Teddy Bhullar and Ebenezer Asante -- see source URL]

Minister of Health Dr. Agnes Binagwaho said: "The campaign being launched in Rwanda today [14 Dec 2014] is an important milestone toward mobilising resources to help our sister African countries devastated by the Ebola outbreak. It is great to see telecom companies come together in efforts to avert the spread of the virus." He was addressing the media at a joint telecom press conference in Kigali last week. These telecommunication companies join the rest across the continent under an initiative dubbed "The Ebola Solidarity Campaign" which will use a SMS dedicated platform to raise funds from citizens for the deployment of African health workers to affected countries.... -- more

[Byline: Agnes Bateta]

